static.report.forecastErrorMonthlyFormul: Only months that have both a forecast and an actual consumption record are included in the forecast error calculation. The column to the right of the forecast error details how many months were included in that calculation.
The forecast error can go above 100% and the higher the %, the worse the forecast is.

A planning unit labeled ` No months in this period contain both forecast and actual consumption ` means that there are no months in the selected time window that have both actual and forecast records in the same month.
A planning unit labeled ` Total actual consumption for last 6 months = 0` means that the summation of the actual consumption for the usable months in the selected time window was 0.
The WAPE formula is using the previous 3-12 months of data depending on the selection in the ‘Time Window’ dropdown.

A month labeled `No months in this period contain both forecast and actual consumption` means that there are no months in the selected time window that have both actual and forecast records in the same month.
A month labeled `Total actual consumption for last 6 months = 0` means that the summation of the actual consumption for the usable months in the selected time window was 0.
